# Troposphere
The troposphere is the lowest layer of the atmosphere. It is the layer where the weather occurs. The air is warmest and most dense at the bottom and cooler and less dense as you go up. 

# Stratosphere
The stratosphere is the second layer of the atmosphere. It is above the troposphere and below the mesosphere. The air is very stable and does not change much. The ozone layer is found in the stratosphere and protects the Earth from harmful ultraviolet radiation. 

# Mesosphere
The mesosphere is the third layer of the atmosphere. It is above the stratosphere and below the thermosphere. The air is colder and less dense as you go up. This layer is where meteors burn up and where aurorae occur. 

# Thermosphere
The thermosphere is the fourth layer of the atmosphere
